<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 91.71 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Friday lost 91.71 points to 3,089.02
as against Thursday's close of 3,180.73.
</P>
<P>
The national index also fell by 38.04 points to 1,355.70 from
the previous close of 1,393.74.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted down at 309.01
and 121.08 compared with the previous close of 317.36 and 124.73
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities suffered a fresh setback pushing the sensitive index
sharply down by over 91 points on the last day of the current
settlement on BSE market Friday due to sustained bull liquidation
and lack of worthwhile support from institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The market, which was affected due to the political uncertainty
during the last couple of days, encountered fresh selling pressure
in the form of squaring up business and investors' disinterest in
the light of fresh margins by the securities and exchange board of
India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
