<HEADLINE> Chinese President Greets New S. African Communist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, who is also General Secretary of the ruling Communist
Party of China (CPC), on Friday congratulated Blade Nzimande on
his election as chief of the South African Communist Party
(SACP).
</P>
<P>
In a message to Nzimande, Jiang said he was delighted at his
election as the SACP General Secretary on Thursday at the 10th
national congress of the party.
</P>
<P>
"I wish to extend to you sincere congratulations on behalf of
the Communist Party of China and on my own behalf," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"The SACP, as a party with a glorious tradition of
revolutionary struggles, has made outstanding contributions to
the abolition of apartheid in South Africa, and is now playing an
important role in the new South Africa's democratic advancement.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that under your leadership, the SACP will
continue to score new achievements on its way forward," said the
CPC leader.
</P>
<P>
Jiang wished Nzimande success in fulfilling the lofty missions
entrusted by the 10th Congress of the SACP.  
</P>
