<HEADLINE> Envoy of Pakistan PM to Visit Nepal Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Akram Zaki, the special envoy of
Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, is scheduled to arrive here
Saturday for a five-day visit, the Pakistani Embassy said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Zaki will discuss with Nepali leaders a wide range of issues,
the embassy said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
He will be carrying a letter from Sharif to his Nepalese
counterpart Girija Prasad Koirala, the embassy said.
</P>
<P>
Zaki will also visit Bangladesh, Sri Lanka and the Maldives.
</P>
<P>
The visit comes after India and Pakistan conducted nuclear
tests in May and prior to the 10th summit of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) to be held late this
month in Colombo, Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, formed in December 1985, groups Bangladesh, Bhutan,
India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
