<HEADLINE> Italy Force France into Another Extra-time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Italy held hosts France to their
second extra-time in the first quarter-final match at the World Cup
finals here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The French team had experienced an extra-time victory in the
round of 16 when they beat Paraguay 1-0 with a golden goal.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team fought a defensive game against the hosts and
only in the last 25 minutes of the regulation time they began to
enjoy an upper hand in the midfield.
</P>
<P>
The French team ran hard in the 90 minutes and seemed a little
bit tired in the last minutes and that enabled the Italian team
launch several counter-attacks. 
