<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thon Vows to Get Position Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Olaf Thon has vowed to get back
his libero position which had been grabbed by veteran Lothar Matthaus.
</P>
<P>
"I will do all it takes to get my position back," said the Schalke
04 midfielder in Nice on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
But he refused to comment on the performance of Matthaus, who had
appeared pivotal in the latest games.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know whether Lothar is the best man in this position. I'm
not qualified to answer that question," said Thon.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the media relations, he said: "I'm not paranoid. I don't
think I have been the victim of a media campaign in favor of
Matthaus."
</P>
<P>
"The World Cup is a very demanding championship. And it's normal
that there is some rotation of players." 
</P>
</TEXT>
