<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 16:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heart Disease Main Killer in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Heart disease has been the main
killer in Cyprus since more than 50 percent of Cypriot deaths are
heart-related, a local cardiologist said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Launching a new book by the Cyprus Heart Foundation "Coronary
Heart Disease -- What You Should Know About it," Dr. Pambis
Nicolaides told reporters that Cyprus has the highest number of
cardiologists per capita in Europe and offers high-standard
diagnosis and treatment methods, but prevention is at low levels
as a result of the Cypriot lifestyle.
</P>
<P>
The high number of smokers on the island, estimated at about 24
percent of the 850,000 population, unhealthy diet and lack of
exercise are the main reasons Cypriots develop heart disease, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He quoted a survey as showing about 4 percent of elementary
school children, 16 percent of high school students, 55 percent in
technical schools and 12 percent of Cyprus University students
smoke.
</P>
<P>
According to World Health Organization (WHO) figures, 12
million people worldwide die prematurely every year as a result
of heart failure and half of these deaths can be avoided.
</P>
<P>
The WHO figures also show that two thirds of the reduction in
deaths from heart related problems are due to prevention and only
one third to modern treatment methods.
</P>
<P>
Nicolaides said the aim of the book is to increase public
awareness on heart-related diseases.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Cyprus Heart Foundation hopes to create an
independent heart center on the island in the future, so that
Cypriot heart patients can be operated on locally in the best
possible conditions and Cyprus becomes a regional cardio-surgical
center.
</P>
<P>
An island-wide study on coronary heart disease will also be
carried out by the foundation in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
