<HEADLINE> Cambodia Launches Voter Education Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's National Election
committee (NEC) has launched a voter education campaign, aimed at
informing voters about procedures for casting a ballot on July 26,
and for assuring them that their votes will be secret.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 copies of a first NEC leaflet giving general
information of the polls have been distributed nationwide with the
help of independent, non-government organizations.
</P>
<P>
A poster depicting all 39 political parties and their logos was
produced as part of the campaign to help voters, especially
illiterate voters, identify the party they will choose.
</P>
<P>
Illiterate voters will not be allowed to ask for help in
reading the ballot paper. Therefore it is very important that as
many people as possible are able to study this poster.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 copies have been printed. They will be
distributed to all the provinces this week. Two more leaflets and
one other poster dealing with the secrecy of the vote, and
procedures for casting a ballot, will be distributed by the end of
next week.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, eight theater troupes financed by the
European Union began on Friday to stage performances explaining
the voting procedures and assuring voters that the ballots will be
cast in secret. The actors will tour 11 provinces over 21 days.
</P>
<P>
Television and radio programs explaining voting procedures and
other related information will be broadcast for the first time on
Tuesday July 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
