<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Advance after Penalty Shoot-out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Hosts France advanced into the
semi-finals of France'98 after beating Italy 4-3 in the penalty
shoot-out here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Italian midfielder Luigi di Biagio's attempt hit the cross-bar
and that was the end of the Italian team's campaign in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The two teams each had one shot saved by the opponent
goal-keeper in the first three round of shoot-out. Laurent Blanc,
who put France through to the quarter-finals with a golden goal in
the match against Paraguay, made no mistake in netting his shot to
put France 4-3 ahead.
</P>
<P>
Biagio, who had put up a good performance in the match, released
a fierce shot with his right foot. The French goal-keeper could do
nothing but the ball hit the cross-bar and bounced out.
</P>
<P>
Before the shoot-out, the Italian team had very good chance to
get a golden goal but Roberto Baggio, who replaced Alessandro del
Piero in the second half, put his shot just wide.
</P>
<P>
The French team dominated the first half of the regulation time.
With the return of play-maker Zinedine Zidane, they enjoyed a great
advantage in the midfield.
</P>
<P>
The Italian team played solidly in defense while the French
forwards could not find the way to break up the Italian defense line.
</P>
<P>
The Italian goal-keeper Gianluca Pagliuca put up several brave
saves in the first 15 minutes of the match to disallow the shots
from Zidane and Emmanuel Petit.
</P>
<P>
However, when the match went into the second half, the French
team appeared tired and gradually lost the domination of midfield,
especially after Roberto Baggio went onto the pitch at the 67th minute.
</P>
<P>
Baggio gave the Italian team immediately advantage in the
midfield and threatened the French goal with acute crosses.
</P>
<P>
But the Italian forward Christian Vieri, who shared the top
place with Argentine Bastituta in the scorers' list with 5 goals,
failed to show his flair and missed a handful of chances.
</P>
<P>
After the 90-minute regulation time, both teams were exhausted
and could not organise their attacks.
</P>
<P>
It was the second penalty shoot-out in the France'98 World Cup
finals. Earlier in a second round match, Argentina eliminated
England, also with penalty shoot-out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Emphasizes Nuclear Deterrent Role in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Friday highlighted role of the nuclear deterrent in ensuring the
country's security and called for development of the strategic
nuclear forces.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular meeting of the Russian Security Council,
Yeltsin said the nuclear deterrent was a key element ensuring
Russian national security, according to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
"The nuclear forces are among the most important factors
contributing to our country's security," the president stated.
</P>
<P>
He, meanwhile, refuted the idea that Russia has become weaker
in the nuclear domain.
</P>
<P>
President's spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky quoted Yeltsin as
saying that Russia attached prime importance to the START-2
treaty, and in case of its ratification it would be a serious
measure aimed at global strategic stability.
</P>
<P>
The outline of a START-3 treaty was ready, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
According to Yastrzhembsky, Yeltsin is set to attach particular
importance to the development of the Russian strategic nuclear
force.
</P>
<P>
The nation's strategic forces were fully controllable, but the
issue of the "natural aging " of sea, land, and air components of
nuclear weapons is already rising, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that special attention should be paid to the problems
of the nuclear defense sector and the missile industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
