<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK National Exporters Database Goes On-Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The UK's first ever
Government-supported National Exporters Database was launched
Friday on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
The database has an initial 52,000 entries although it is
expected this number will increase as the service becomes more
widely marketed.
</P>
<P>
The database will be operated by the Dialog Corporation plc on
behalf of the Government and comprises phase one of an expanded
TradeUK project, the Department of Trade and Industry said.
</P>
<P>
From September TradeUK will also include a revised Export Sales
Leads Service which will deliver leads from Foreign Office
commercial staff abroad to UK exporters via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the new service on its launching, Lord Clinton-Davis,
the Minister of Trade, said: "It is a prime example of our
determination and commitment to see UK firms take advantage of the
significant advances in information technology, especially the
Internet."
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the database will enable any UK exporter to
have a detailed entry on a database which potentially can be seen
by any buyer in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
