<HEADLINE> Blair Pledges to Work for Release of British Hostages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
pledged here Friday that his Labor government would make all its
efforts to release the two British hostages held in Chechnya,
Russia.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the families of British aid workers Camilla Carr
and Jon James, Blair said: "I can only begin to imagine the strain
you must all be under. I want you to know now that the government
will continue to do all it can to secure their release."
</P>
<P>
Early Friday, British Foreign Office minister Liz Symons held
talks with the families of the two aid workers and told them there
was still no positive news.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that hundreds of people have been abducted by
criminal groups in Chechnya over the past few years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
