<HEADLINE> President: Turkey Supports Right of Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here Friday Turkey always supports the right of the
Palestinian people, Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with visiting Palestinian Minister for Jerusalem
Affairs Faisal Husseini, Demirel said that it is useful for Turkey
and Palestine to exchange views and for Turkey to learn the
developments in Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Husseini, who arrived here Thursday on a three-day visit, said
that he is here to discuss some important issues concerning
Jerusalem with Turkish officials.
</P>
<P>
"Jerusalem is in danger," he said, indicating recent Israeli
bid to expand the municipal borders of the city.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian minister said that Israel's attempt to that
effect might endanger not only the Middle East peace process but
the future of the mixed demographic status of the holy city.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Palestinian researchers could be
allowed to use the archives pertaining to Jerusalem during the
Ottoman Empire period.
</P>
<P>
Husseini also held talks with Turkish State Minister Sukru Sina
Gurel and Foreign Minister Ismail Cem who is scheduled to visit
Palestine next week.
</P>
<P>
Husseini's tour also aims to make preparations for Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat's upcoming visit to Turkey at the end of the
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
