<HEADLINE> Turkish PM to Visit Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz
is to pay an official visit to Macedonia from July 6 to 7, the
first one by a Turkish prime minister to the Balkan nation since
its independence in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relations and regional issues, especially the Kosovo
crisis, are expected to be taken up during the visit, a Turkish
Foreign Ministry written statement said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a social welfare protocol will be signed by the two
governments.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has always attached great importance to establishing
good relations with Macedonia and supported its efforts to
integrate with the international community, said the
statement. 
</P>
