<HEADLINE> Brown on British Membership of Single European Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- British Chancellor of the Exchequer
Gordon Brown indicated Friday that Britain could join the European
Monetary Union (EMU) over the next few days.
</P>
<P>
Brown said in a letter to the parliament's Treasury Committee:"
With our program of economic reforms and business preparations, it
is realistic to think that the economy could be in a position to
allow the UK to join the single currency early in the next
parliament."
</P>
<P>
"The program of economic reforms which the government has
introduced is both in the national economic interest and will help
Britain to meet the economic tests," Brown said.
</P>
<P>
The Chancellor stressed that Britain's financial services
industry would benefit from the membership of the single currency,
promoting investment and jobs creation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
