<HEADLINE> Ugandan Deputy PM Praises China's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Second Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Tourism, Trade and Industry Moses Ali
Friday praised the tremendous economic achievements China has
made over the last two decades.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister said this to Chinese Ambassador to
Uganda Song Zengshou Friday evening at a dinner party hosted by
the Chinese.
</P>
<P>
"Although China and Uganda are both developing countries,
China has made tremendous development and achievements in fields
of industry, trade, tourism, and agriculture," Ali said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese products have entered markets of many other countries,
he said, and this is because of the appropriate technology used
in production, low cost, high-quality materials and good export
promotion strategy.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister added that Uganda has a lot to learn
from China and this occasion provides a good chance for the
Ugandan business community to know about China and to exchange
information and ideas.
</P>
<P>
He said both countries should further strengthen their trade
and economic links. Uganda would like to trade directly with
China to increase the volume of bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
China is good at small-scale industries, he acknowledged, and
his ministry is prepared to learn from China's experience in this
aspect.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's tourism industry is small but growing and Ali said
that he would appreciate it if Chinese businessmen could invest
in this sector in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister, accompanied by other officials and
businessmen of his country, also thanked the Chinese government
for the assistance China has been giving and continues to give to
Uganda in many fields. 
