<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Novotna Snatches Wimbledon Women's Singles Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Czech tennis veteran Jana Novotna
snatched her first Wimbledon after beating her French opponent
Nathalie Tauziat in straight sets at the women's singles final
clash of the Wimbledon Tennis Championships.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Novotna, the Wimbledon runner-up in 1992 and
1997, was nervous at the beginning of the first set and lost her
first service to her opponent. Gradually consolidating her
position at the Center Court, Novotna launched aggressive attacks
and won the first set 6:4.
</P>
<P>
Reluctant to give up her golden chance to become a Wimbledon
Champion, 30-year-old Tauziat defended brilliantly and displayed
some top class tennis. However, an energetic Novotna held her
position firmly and finally won the crucial second set 7:5.
</P>
</TEXT>
