<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Cut Oil Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia will cut the export quotas of
four Russian oil companies by one third over the third quarter of
this year, the Interfax news agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Russia will export 28.2 million tonnes of oil in the third
quarter, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The four companies are Onako, Sidanko (the Varyeganneft
subsidiary), Tatneft and Bashneft.
</P>
<P>
Russia has agreed to cut its oil production and exports to join
the efforts of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC) to boost oil prices on the world market.
</P>
<P>
Russian Fuel and Energy Minister Sergei Generalov said the
action may help increase demand for oil and petroleum products not
only on international markets but also on the Russian domestic
market.
</P>
<P>
The sluggish world oil market, which has lasted for months, has
brought huge economic losses for Russia, a big oil producer of
around six million barrels of oil a day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
