<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Died in Traffic Accident in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Three Zimbabweans were killed on
the spot and six others injured early Saturday morning when a
Mutare city bound commuter bus collided with a train heading for
Harare at a rail crossing in Mutare, east Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
One of the survivors, Lovemore Manzvi, said the train driver
hooted before approaching the rail crossing but the driver of the
commuter bus which carried eight passengers did not stop, the
Zimbabwe News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Manzvi said it was at that time when the train hit the right
front side of the commuter bus, sending it into the air before
landing on its side about five meters away from the rail
crossing.
</P>
<P>
The fatal accident occurs barely three months after Mutare's
Mayor Lawrence Mudewhe convened a meeting with police and
commuter bus operators in which he warned about reckless driving.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, a six-member committee comprising police,
city council and commuter bus operators was set up to find ways
of curbing the soaring road accidents involving commuter buses.
</P>
</TEXT>
