<HEADLINE> Bugner Wins WBF Heavyweight Title After Smith Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Joe Bugner took the vacant World
Boxing Federation (WBF) heavyweight title after his American
opponent James "Bonecrusher" Smith withdrew before the start of
the second round in Gold Coast of Australia Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Smith, 45, dislocated his right shoulder in a flurry of
punches in the opening round and was unable to continue when the
bell sounded for the start of the second round.
</P>
<P>
Australian-based Bugner, 48, whose only other world title fight
was almost 23 years ago when he lost on a points decision to
Muhammad Ali, thanked his fans.
</P>
<P>
Smith said he would like to come back in October and challenge
Bugner for the title. 
</P>
