<HEADLINE> Chinese Courts Urged to Provide Guarantee for Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Justice Xiao Yang
has urged courts at all levels to provide a judicial guarantee for
the realization of the country's economic growth target this year.
</P>
<P>
"Courts at all levels must do a good job in the administration
of justice and ... resolutely safeguard social stability to
provide a judicial guarantee for the realization of this year's
economic growth target," Xiao said recently.
</P>
<P>
China has set this year's growth rate for its gross domestic
product at 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Performing a good job in the administration of justice and
safeguarding stability are the overwhelmingly important tasks of
the people's courts at the current stage," he said.
</P>
<P>
Right now, earnest efforts must be made to implement the
revised Criminal Law and the Criminal Procedural Law and deal a
harsh blow to serious crimes that threaten social stability, Xiao
said.
</P>
<P>
"We should use the justice administration function to readjust
the relation between civil and economic affairs and eliminate
all sorts of social contradictions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Using judicial means to guarantee the smooth implementation of
major reform measures and the realization of the national economic
growth target is a concrete reflection of justice administration
serving the whole situation of the Party and the state, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of this year, special efforts must be made
to ensure a good job by the justice administration of cases
pertaining to financial disputes, state-owned enterprise reforms,
farmland contracting, agricultural development, real estate, labor
disputes and social guarantees, Xiao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
