<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France First Host to Win Penalty Shoot-out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- France is the first host country to win a
penalty shoot-out in the history of the World Cup finals, FIFA said
here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
FIFA spokesman Keith Cooper said the 4-3 win came after Mexico's
loss to West Germany in the quarterfinals in 1986 and Italy's defeat
by Argentina in the 1990 semifinals, both on penalty shootouts.
</P>
<P>
He said Friday's game was the 12th in World Cup that had to resort
to penalty shootouts to decide the winners.
</P>
<P>
Overall there have been 123 spot kicks in these shootouts, with 97
resulting in a goal, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
