<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Volcanic Island Found in Coastal Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A volcanic island has been found in
Zhangpu County of coastal Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Located two kilometers off the coast, the uninhabited Linjinyu
island covers an area of 0.16 square kilometers, with
forest-covered mountains in the center. It is 72.7 meters above
sea level.
</P>
<P>
Running springs and roaming goats can be found everywhere on
the island, which is surrounded by all kinds of huge rocks taking
shapes during volcanic eruptions.
</P>
<P>
The island has many small craters and trails left by volcanic
eruptions and rolling lava formed centuries before, said
geologists who have made several visits to the island.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
