<HEADLINE> Unity among Ethnic Groups Celebrated in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The municipality government today
organized a publicity activity to help local residents become more
aware of the importance of unity among the country's various
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
More than 40,000 brochures were given to passers-by showing the
progress in economy, culture, education, art and sports by ethnic
groups living in the Chinese capital during recent years.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has 480,000 people from China's 55 ethnic groups,
making up 3.84 percent of the city's total population.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic groups such as Hui, Manchu, Mongolian, Korean, Zhuang,
Uygur, Miao, Tujia and Tibetan each reportedly has more than 1,000
people living in Beijing. 
