<HEADLINE> '98 Shanghai Tourism Festival to Open on Oct. 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Shanghai Tourism Festival
will be held from October 17 to November 8, said an official of
the city's tourism authority today.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's festival, which first started in 1990,
is "New Shanghai, New Feelings,", aiming to highlight the modern
city scenery and prosperous trading in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The festival will begin with a morning run of 1,000
participants instead of the large evening party held in previous
years, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The 20-day celebration will include a wedding ceremony,
campfire party, carnival and gala parade.
</P>
<P>
The '98 China International Tourism Fair will also be held
during the festival in Shanghai, and is expected to attract nearly
10,000 overseas traders and tourists. Thirty Chinese provinces and
cities have reportedly organized delegations for the fair.
</P>
<P>
Computer users can get information about the festival on the
Internet, said the official. 
</P>
