<HEADLINE> NPC Official Urges Strict Implementation of Taxation Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Tian Jiyun, Vice-Chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), today
urged the taxation law-enforcement inspection teams nationwide to
seriously and effectively carry out their work.
</P>
<P>
Tian, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China, made the call during a
visit to southwestern China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Taxes are a major source for the country's revenue, he said, so
the enforcement of the Law on Administration of Taxation is very
important for China's economic growth and social development.
</P>
<P>
Tian stressed that law enforcement must be taken seriously and
in a down-to-earth manner.
</P>
<P>
From June 30 to July 4, Tian visited the construction sites of
the 1999 World Garden Fair, the Kunming International Trade Center
and the Dianchi Lake water pollution control project. He also
heard reports on the enforcement of the taxation law in Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
He said paying taxes is the duty of each enterprise and
individual. The major infrastructure projects, social welfare
programs, national defense, aid to the poor, disaster-relief work
and many other projects depend on revenue.
</P>
<P>
A NPC inspection team will complete a taxation law-enforcement
inspection in several prefectures in Yunnan soon. 
</P>
