<HEADLINE> FIFA Praises Frenchman for Sportsmanship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- FIFA on Saturday praised France's
Emmanuel Petit for his sportsmanship in a World Cup quarterfinal
against Italy.
</P>
<P>
FIFA spokesman Keith Cooper said his organization would consider
Petit as a candidate for the annual Fair Play award this year.
</P>
<P>
Cooper said, "We would like to officially commend Emmanuel Petit
for this gesture of outstanding sportsmanship."
</P>
<P>
He added, "No doubt this will make him one of the candidates by the
end of the year for the annual FIFA Fair Play Award."
</P>
<P>
Cooper said, Petit had been in a very promising position,
possessing the ball at one time during the heatly-contested game at
the Stade de France on Friday.
</P>
<P>
But Petit deliberately put the ball out of play because he saw an
Italian player was injured and in need of medical attention, said
Cooper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
