<HEADLINE> Chinese President Leaves for Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin left
here for home on Saturday after a five-nation meeting and a
working visit to Kazakstan.
</P>
<P>
In the five-nation meeting, China, Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan,
Russia and Tajikistan issued a joint statement, committing
themselves to preventing their territories from being used to harm
each other's sovereignty, security and social order.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that to expand and strengthen bilateral and
multilateral cooperation among them is in the best interests of
their own peoples.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, President Jiang paid an one-day working
visit to Kazakstan.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President signed with his counterpart of Kazakstan
Nursultan Nazarbayev a complementary agreement on the border
issues between the two countries. 
</P>
