<HEADLINE> HK Police Fully Prepared for New Airport Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chek Lap Kok (CLK) Police Station
has been fully equipped and prepared to maintain effective
policing and public order in the new airport, a senior police
officer said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the CLK Police Station, Chief Inspector (Operation)
of CLK District Li Cheuk-wai said: "Following the deployment of
the final batch of 160 uniformed police officers on June 15, the
manpower of the CLK police station has reached its present
strength of 397."
</P>
<P>
"In the past few weeks, these 160 officers have received
various kinds of training to familiarize them with the new working
environment," he said.
</P>
<P>
The training included lectures by government departments such
as the Immigration Department and Customs and Excise Department,
airliner, cargo and catering companies, as well as site visits.
</P>
<P>
They were also briefed on contingency plans related to aircraft
accidents and terrorist situations, the senior inspector said.
</P>
<P>
To put theory into practice, the officers took part in various
exercises simulating terrorist attacks or other accidents over the
past few weeks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 160 officers who lately joined the CLK District, 50 were
formally attached to the Kai Tak Airport District, bringing with
them working experience in the airport, he added.
</P>
<P>
The CLK Police District will be officially retitled as the
Airport District next Monday when the multi-billion-dollar new
airport is put into operation.
</P>
<P>
"Starting from next Monday, the new Airport District will be
operating at the new airport as effectively and professionally as
Kai Tak," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
Officers of the Patrol Sub-units will be covering the whole
airport to prevent crime and respond to any possible incidents,
while Crime and Task Force officers will detect and combat crime.
</P>
</TEXT>
