<HEADLINE> Fall in India's Foreign Currency Assets Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Fall in India's foreign currency
assets (FCA) has continued with a drop of 219 million U.S. dollars
in the week ending June 26 this year, said a weekly statistical
supplement of the Reserve Bank of India here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
FCA as on June 26 amounted to 24,104 million U.S. dollars, down
by 1,871 million from end-March 1998 level.
</P>
<P>
With special drawing rights (SDRS) declining by 39 million
dollars during the week, the total foreign exchange reserves have
dropped by 258 million to 27,283 million dollars. 
</P>
