<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Back in China after Working Visit to Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin wound
up his working visit to Kazakhstan and returned to Urumqi, the
capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang set off on July 3 for Alma-Ata of Kazakhstan to attend
the five-nation meeting of China, Kazakhstan, Kyrghyzstan, Russia
and Tajikistan, at the invitation of Kazakhstan President
Nursultan Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
The meeting mainly discussed such issues as regional security
and economic cooperation, and ended with the issue of a joint
declaration.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Alma-Ata, President Jiang held talks with
Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev, and they had an
in-depth exchange of views and reached extensive consensus
concerning the development of bilateral relations oriented to the
21st century and other international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents signed the second supplement to the Border
Demarcation Agreement between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang also met separately with Kyrghyzstan President
Askar Akayev, Tajikistan President Emomali Rakhmonov, and Russian
Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov who came to the meeting on
behalf of President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang's entourage, which included Wang Yeping,
Jiang's wife, Vice-Premier Qian Qichen and his wife Zhou Hanqiong,
Zeng Qinghong, member of the Secretariate of the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and concurrently director of
the General Office of the CPC Central Committee, Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan, Zeng Peiyan, minister in charge of the State
Development Planning Commission, Teng Wensheng, director of the
Policy Research Office of the CPC Central Committee, Zhang
Deguang, vice-foreign minister, You Xigui, deputy director of the
General Office of the CPC Central Committee, and Jia Ting'an,
director of the General Office of Jiang Zemin, also returned to
Urumqi aboard the same plane.
</P>
<P>
When President Jiang an his wife alighted from plane, two
children stepped forward to present them with flowers, and local
people of various nationalities and performing artists sang and
danced to congratulate Jiang on his successful visit.
</P>
<P>
Local officials who met President Jiang Zemin at airport
included Wang Lequan, secretary of the CPC Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Regional Committee, Abdul'ahat Abdurixit, chairman of
the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Regional Government, and other
senior officials from the Lanzhou Military Area Command and
Autonomous Regional People's Congress of Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
Amongst those who saw President Jiang off in Alma-Ata upon his
leaving were Kazakhstan President and Mrs. Nazarbayev, and Li Hui,
Chinese ambassador to Kazakhstan, and representatives of resident
Chinese trade and banking agencies in Kazakhstan. 
</P>
