<HEADLINE> Kazakh President Hosts Banquet for Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan President Nursultan
Nazarbayev gave a banquet here Sunday in honor of visiting Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said in his toast that since the establishment of
diplomatic relations, Kazakhstan and China have brought their
economic, scientific and cultural cooperation to a new level.
</P>
<P>
But he noted that the most important achievement of all is the
agreement the two countries have reached on the most complex issue
of border demarcation.
</P>
<P>
"The signing of a complementary agreement on the remaining two
sections of the border is a manifestation of the mutual understanding
and good will of our two countries," Nazarbayev said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the signing of the agreement will lay a solid
foundation for the two countries to pursue bolder programs, seek
common prosperity and deepen friendship.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang said in reply that the two countries have been
on very good terms by fostering good-neighborliness and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the complete settlement of border issues is a
result of the efforts of both countries to deepen their mutual
trust and understanding.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that as long as the two countries based their
relations on equal consultation and mutual accommodation, any
complex problem can be solved. 
</P>
