<HEADLINE> Intel to Suspend Production for 10 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Intel, the world's largest chip
maker, will begin a temporary suspension of production at two chip
assembly plants in Hillsboro, Oregan for about 10 days, beginning
this holiday weekend, according to reports from the company.
</P>
<P>
"This is a warm-down to reduce the inventory of older
products", Intel spokesman Tom Waldrop said Thursday. "You don't
shut the plant down, you suspend production."
</P>
<P>
About 1,700 employees work in the two plants and Intel said
that most of them will take 10 days off without pay.
</P>
<P>
The news of a manufacturing cutback comes amid rumors
circulating on Wall Street over the past few days that Intel may
announce further job cuts, or even layoffs, in addition to the
3,000 layoffs already announced.
</P>
<P>
Industry sources noted that the California-based chip maker has
been under pressure from the relentless price cuts in the personal
computer industry and it has also quickened the pace of price cuts
for all its chips in recent months.
</P>
<P>
Intel, as well as the entire semiconductor industry, is also
hurt by the current economic crisis in Asia, they said, adding
that some semiconductor makers have announced layoffs or early
retirement packages in efforts to cut costs and staff amid
sluggish demand for chips. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
