<HEADLINE> Nigeria's New Chief of General Staff Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's former Chief of Naval
Staff Rear Admiral Ikahai Mike Akhigbe has been appointed the
chief of general staff, replacing Oladipo Diya, who was sentenced
to death two months ago for coup plotting.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued in the capital Abuja Friday night
announcing the appointment of Nigeria's No. 2 position, also
named Air-Vice Marshal Alami Dagash as the new chief of defense
staff.
</P>
<P>
Daggash, the commander of the Nigerian Defense Academy until
the appointment, succeeds General Abdulsalam Abubakar who is now
the Head of State and Commander-In-Chief of the Armed Forces of
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was the chief of defense staff until his appointment
on June 9 as head of state following the sudden death of General
Sani Abacha the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Akhigbe was born on September 29, 1946 in Fugar, southern Edo
State. After graduation from the Nigerian Defense Academy, he
took courses on naval technology, weapons and operations in
India, Italy, the Netherlands, Britain and Germany in early
1970s.
</P>
<P>
He was once appointed governor of Lagos State, the then
national capital, in late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
With the new appointment, Akhigbe is expected to reduce the
burden on the office of the head of state which took over the
schedule following Diya's removal.
</P>
<P>
Daggash will also coordinate the affairs of the three arms of
the military. But it was unclear Friday night if he would
combine his schedule with that of the minister of defense, a
position held by General Abacha until his death.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
