<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Tax Collections up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Kenya Revenue Authority (KRA)
collected 154 billion Kenyan Shillings (2.6 billion U.S. Dollars)
from tax-payers during the 1997/98 fiscal year (July/June), up 18
percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The collections in the 1996/97 fiscal year stood at 130.6
billion Shillings (2.2 billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The hike was due to improved management of tax collections by
the authority, KRA Commissioner-General John Msafari was quoted
by the Daily Nation newspaper Saturday as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said in a statement that there was an increased voluntary
compliance by taxpayers, as well as more effective enforcement.
</P>
<P>
There was also a reduction in dumping of uncustomed goods and
an increased field audit by KRA, as opposed to desk audits which
are prone to manipulation by some tax-payers, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The authority had established a large taxpayer unit to deal
with corporate clients with a turnover in excess of 500 million
Shillings and an investigations unit to fight multiple tax
evasion.
</P>
<P>
During the 1997/98 fiscal year, KRA collected a total of 78.2
billion Shillings (1.3 billion Dollars) from Customs and Excise,
which were 2.2 billion Shillings above the target.
</P>
<P>
Income tax brought in 56.4 billion Shillings which were over
one billion Shillings above the target. But earnings from road
transport fell short of the target of 1.38 billion Shillings by
411 million Shillings.
</P>
<P>
However, "The 1998/99 financial year is going to be even more
challenging as we are aiming at generating much more revenue for
the government, economic uncertainties notwithstanding," said
Msafari.
</P>
<P>
In the 1998/99 budget announced last month, Finance Minister
Simeon Nyachae said the independence of KRA would be enhanced by
reducing the number of board members from the public sector while
raising the number of members from the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The independence of KRA was one of the pre-conditions set by
donors before the resumption of aid.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0143 </DOCNO>
