<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 24,000 Herd of Cattle Stolen in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 24,000 herd of cattle
worth about 3.4 million U.S. Dollars have been stolen from
commercial farms in Zimbabwe in the last two years.
</P>
<P>
The Cattle Producers' Association (CPA) told The Herald daily
Friday that a herd of 10,220 was stolen in 1996 while 10,117 was
stolen last year. Nearly 4,000 cattle have been stolen so far
this year.
</P>
<P>
The association said the recovery rate of 18 percent was
"nothing short of pathetic," the Daily Herald reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The farmers and an insurance company had jointly launched a
police stock-theft station of the month to motivate police
stations to investigate stock-theft more seriously.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the CPA has deplored delays by South Africa to
allow Zimbabwe's live exports, 1,500 tons of processed beef
products and a beef quota of 5,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The CPA said it had lost multi-million Dollar export
opportunities because of the delays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
