<HEADLINE> Sino-Kazakh Border Issues Completely Solved: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here Saturday that China and Kazakhstan have thoroughly solved the
border issues between them.
</P>
<P>
In line with the principles of equal consultation and mutual
understanding, the two sides have reached agreement on all the
remaining border issues, which represents a complete resolution to
them, said Jiang while meeting with his Kazakh counterpart
Nursultan Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
Border issues are always very sensative and complicated in
international relations and, if not properly solved, can often
trigger conflicts, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said the smooth settlement of the border issues will greatly
deepen the mutual trust and friendship between the two countries,
and will have a positive impact on their efforts to solve border
issues with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev said that the supplementary border agreement is a
very important document, which represents a complete solution to
the remaining border issues between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China and Kazakhstan signed a border agreement in April 1994
and a supplementary border agreement in July 1996.
</P>
<P>
On trade relations, Nazarbayev said that China has become a
very important trade partner to Kazakhstan thanks to the signing
of a series of cooperation agreements in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the two countries should intensify their
mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two presidents also reiterated their
firm opposition to national splittism, saying that the two
countries will crack down on terrorist activities and safeguard
regional stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
