<HEADLINE> China Expects Sound Development of Sino-Kazakh Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here Saturday that he is fully confident of a sound development of
the good-neighborly relations between China and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a banquet held in his honor by Kazakh President
Nursultan Nazarbayev, Jiang said the Chinese people have long
cherished friendship with the Kazakh people.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of diplomatic ties more than six years
ago, there has been a steady and healthy development in the
relations between the two countries on the track of
good-neighborliness, friendship and mutually beneficial
cooperation, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The border issues between them have been thoroughly solved as
well, he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted it has been proved that the two countries are capable
of solving any complicated issues between them as long as they
observe the principles of consultation based on equality, mutual
understanding and respecting mutual interests.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of Nazarbayev, Jiang said, Kazakhstan has
been enjoying social stability and economic revival. The country
has undergone profound and inspiring changes.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his confidence in the development of bilateral
ties in the new century and called for unremitting efforts on both
sides to work for their lasting friendship. 
</P>
