<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US-Funded Projects Flourish in South China's City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- US-funded projects in Guangzhou,
the capital of south China's Guangdong Province, recorded a total
1997 output value of over 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's 273 US-funded projects involve a combined
contractual investment of some 1.03 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 95 US-funded enterprises have opened offices in Guangzhou,
including two banks and six insurance companies, and 21
American companies on the world's top 500 list have invested in
the city.
</P>
<P>
A total of 194 companies, or 80 percent of the total US-funded
projects in Guangzhou, have invested in the manufacturing industry
and have contributed greatly to improving and upgrading the city's
light industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou continues to draw an increasing number of investors
from the United States, with Motorola China Electronics
Co. Ltd. setting up a cooperative mobile telecommunications
venture in June this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
