<HEADLINE> Peruvian President Concludes Vietnam Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
concluded his four-day official visit to Vietnam and left Hanoi
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two countries signed four agreements on
cooperation in the fields of agriculture, fishery, science and
technology and trade.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori met Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong, Communist
Party Leader Le Kha Phieu, Prime Minister Phan Van Khai and
National Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the two countries reaffirmed their determination to
raise bilateral relationship to a new height.
</P>
<P>
Phieu reportedly said that Vietnam will push forward its
national industrialization and modernization and expand
international cooperation with other countries.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Peru established diplomatic relations in 1994. The
two-way trade value between the two nations was 25 million
U.S. dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are to join the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum in november this year together with
Russia. 
</P>
