<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Automotive Products Exports Up, but Output Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Car production in Thailand fell by
76.92 percent in the first five months of this year from a year
earlier, but export of automotive products climbed by 80.78
percent, according to the Federation of Thai Industry.
</P>
<P>
Car production in all segments from January to May totaled
49,798 units, down by 165,970 units or 76.92 percent, showed the
federation's figures, which were available Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Motorcycle production for the period totaled 269,872 units,
down by 278,911 units or 50.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports of assembled vehicles were 20,070 units, up by 8,330
units or 70.95 percent. Export value jumped by 5.208 billion baht
(127 million U.S. dollars) or 138.87 percent to 8.959 billion baht
(218 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Exports of car engines were worth 388.9 million baht (9.4
million dollars), down by 329.28 million baht (8.03 million
dollars) or 45.85 percent. Exports of other car parts jumped by
1.021 billion baht (24.9 million dollars) or 181.62 percent to
1.583 billion baht (38.6 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Motorcycle exports reached 94,332 units, up by 37,396 or 65.68
percent while their value rose by 88.95 percent to 3.55 billion
baht (86.5 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
In total, shipments of automotive products for the period were
worth 15.045 billion baht (366.9 million dollars), an increase of
6.705 billion baht (163 million dollars) or 80.78 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
