<HEADLINE> 2,000 Kilograms of Narcotic Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,871 kilograms of
narcotic drugs, including 27 kilograms of heroin, were seized in
Kutkai Township, Northern Shan State of Myanmar, the official
paper The New Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A group comprising members of military columns, Defense
Services Intelligence Unit and Police Force raided two houses in
Koikhan village of Kutkai Township last Saturday and nabbed nine
persons with the narcotic drugs, chemicals, cash and arms, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
Action is taken against the culprits by the authorities, the
paper added.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, in the first four months of
this year, more than 2,600 kilograms of narcotics, including 170
kilograms of heroin, were seized in the country and 8,000 hectares
of poppy plantations and a dozen heroin refineries were destroyed.
 
</P>
