<DOCNO> XIE19980704.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HIV-Infected People on Rise in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- At least 702 people in Indonesia
are known to be infected with the HIV virus which causes AIDS
(Acquired Immunity Deficiency Syndrome), the local press Saturday
quoted a minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 193 are positively suffering from AIDS while the
other 509 are HIV-infected, Coordinating Minister for People's
Welfare/Poverty Alleviation Haryono Suyono told reporters here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said the number of HIV/AIDS sufferers is expected to
increase to 700,000 in the next five years if no serious efforts
are made to fight the spread of the deadly disease.
</P>
<P>
"The figure is based on an expert count, but it could in
reality well be surpasses," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the government is now developing a new,
simple and dynamic strategy, known as communication, information
and education, to counteract the spread of the disease.
</P>
<P>
He said impoverishment of large numbers of Indonesians might
increase the number of HIV-infected people and AIDS sufferers in
the country.
</P>
<P>
"Economic pressure might force more people into prostitution
and thus indirectly raise the number of people running the risk of
being infected with the deadly disease and virus," the minister
added.
</P>
<P>
The poverty rate in Indonesia has gone up from 11 percent to 40
percent or from 22.5 million to 80 million people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
