<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Efficient in Family Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The pursuit of a modern family life
has led to a big reduction in populace and boosted local economy
of east China's Zhejiang province, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The provincial "new family" planning program combining birth
control with building prosperous, happy and healthy families is
popular with the locals. The paper said that its results have also
drawn family planning and population control experts' attention.
</P>
<P>
Data from the provincial government show that by the end of
last year, Zhejiang's population is 44.34 million, 140,000 less
than expected. The birth rate dropped to 11.41 per thousand from
14.76 per thousand in 1992, and the natural population growth rate
stood at 4.93 per thousand last year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the average per-capital income there rose to
7,359 yuan (866 US dollars) in the cities and 3,684 yuan (433 US
dollars) in the countryside last year, ranking fourth and third
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The figures were released yesterday at a national meeting to
study the theory and practice of "new family" planning in Zhejiang
province.
</P>
<P>
With the largest population in the world, China has long worked
hard to feed too many mouths with not enough food and has pursued
population growth control as one measure to thwart potential
disaster.
</P>
<P>
A group of population experts and some local family planning
workers are here assessing the new plan. They will visit some
pilot towns and villages in a number of cities including Shaoxing
and Ningbo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
