<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Central Area Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in its central
area hit 44.9 billion yuan in the first four months of 1998, up
3.3 percent over the same period of 1997, according to the latest
figures from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The top three investment receivers in this area are Hubei,
Henan and Hunan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
