<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Retail Sales Growing up in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's retail sales amounted to
938.8 billion yuan in the first four months of 1998, up 6.9
percent over the same period of 1997, according to the latest
figures from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The top three consumers were Guangdong, Jiangsu and Zhejiang
provinces, with the retail sales standing at 104.4 billion yuan,
73 billion yuan and 62.9 billion yuan, respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
