<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Consumer Prices Rise Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's consumer price index stood
at 99.7 in April, taking the price index for the same period in
1997 as 100, according to the latest figures from the State
Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The price index for fresh vegetables items reached 108.2, which
represented one of the biggest price hikes in the month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
