<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zagallo Happy with Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian coach Mario Zagallo said on
Friday that he was "totally exhausted but happy" after their 3-2 win
over Denmark in the World Cup quarterfinals here.
</P>
<P>
He said: "The first action I did was to call my wife and children
because I wanted to tell them it was such a difficult game."
</P>
<P>
He added, "The Danes could have won 3-2 as well. It's a victory of
will and determination. My players have tried everything to win."
</P>
<P>
"Both teams showed how to play a game in the level of World Cup,
with lots of attacks," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said he did not want to talk about defender Cafu, who will be
banned from the semifinal after collecting a second yellow card
Friday, although the Brazilians have a natural substitution of Ze
Carlos.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo said: "We now have not time for vacationing because the
future games are so close."
</P>
<P>
Cafu said after the game: "I was waiting for the goalkeeper to come
out. I have never been booked in such a situation. Never mind, we will
win the semifinal and I will play in the final."
</P>
<P>
He added, "We really deserve it. We mastered the game completely.
This is the spirit of our game."
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Leonardo also said Denmark played very well.
</P>
<P>
"They played to a very high level. But we played our best game so
far. It was an important step and we're very motivated by the
semifinal game," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
