<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Players Disappointed About Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Italian players were very disappointed
by the penalty shoot-out defeat in the quarter-finals on Friday.
</P>
<P>
It was Italy's third straight penalty shoot-out loss in World Cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
Italian captain Paolo Maldini said:"I've played in three
consecutive World Cup competitions and t's as though history is
repeating itself. I've lost on penalty shoot-outs in a
quarter-final, a semi-final and a final."
</P>
<P>
"France is one of the favorites. They are playing at home and
they also seem to have luck on their side," said Maldini, "Don't
forget that they have scored the most goals so far even though they
didn't convert their chances this evening."
</P>
<P>
Veteran defender Giuseppe Bergomi said:"I am very happy to have
taken part in this World Cup. At my age, it's a bonus. The team
did its best and I think I gave everything I had."
</P>
<P>
Luigi di Biagio, who missed the penalty shot to give France the
victory, said:"It hardly seems fair to lost the World Cup in this
way and to feel in some way personally responsible is a dreadful
feeling. it's been amazing taking part but it's dreadful it ended
like this."
</P>
<P>
Roberto Baggio, who himself missed a penalty shot in the final
against Brazil four years ago, said:"Unfortunately this is the third
time for me. It leaves a very bitter taste. Penalties are the
worst way of all to lose." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
