<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Danish Coach Hard to Believe Team Played So Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Denmark coach Bo Johansson said he could
not believe his players could have played such a good game against
world champions Brazil on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"We were fantastic," he said after their 3-2 quarterfinal loss to
Brazil. "We were almost as good as the best in the world. But, my
players, I had never really believed they were that good."
</P>
<P>
He added, "It's always a shame to lose. But we played a world-class
game. We can be proud of the way we played."
</P>
<P>
Martin Jorgensen, who scored the opening goal for Denmark, said:
"It's not a sad day for Denmark. We showed what we can do. Don't
forget we were playing Brazil. Denmark has got a future." 
</P>
</TEXT>
