<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Criticizes West for Rapprochement With KLA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Greece criticized Friday the Western
countries' efforts for rapprochement with the Kosovo Liberation
Army (KLA), which is trying to win Kosovo's independence from
Yugoslavia by the use of force.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki, Greek
Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos said that the Kosovo crisis
could not be solved through military means but in a political,
peaceful, diplomatic manner by granting the broadest possible
autonomy to Kosovo where ethnic Albanians make up 90 percent of
its nearly 2 million population.
</P>
<P>
While expressing Greece's opposition to Kosovo's independence
from Yugoslavia, he urged Belgrade to agree to full
self-administration for Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The minister also said that Greece fully supported the ethnic
Albanian leader Ibrahim Rugova in proceeding directly to form
integrated institutional support because such a move would upgrade
Rugova himself and his role with a simultaneous obligatory
abandonment of arms by the so-called liberation movement and its
subordination to the political leadership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
