<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Enter World Cup Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazil entered the soccer World Cup
semifinals after a Rivaldo double lifted the world champions to a 3-2
quarterfinal win over Denmark here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The win revenged the Brazilian loss to the same opponents in their
only previous clash in 1989 in Copenhagen, where the Danes won the
friendly 4-0.
</P>
<P>
Denmark stunned the world champions again Friday only two minutes
into the game when Martin Jorgensen scored on a short pass from Brian
Laudrup.
</P>
<P>
Brazil equalized nine minutes later through Bebeto, who slotted the
ball home past Manchester United keeper Peter Schmeichel after
receiving a pass from Inter Milan Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
Brazil led the game for the first time in the 26th minute when
Rivaldo shot in a small angle from left just outside in the box.
</P>
<P>
But Laudrup kept the Danes in the picture by scoring in the 49th
minute and tying the game for the second time.
</P>
<P>
Defender Roberto Carlos had tried to clear the ball with a bicycle
kick but missed. Laudrup made no mistake to collect the ball to score.
</P>
<P>
Rivaldo, who plays for Spanish club side Barcelona, found the net
again in the 60th minute to score the winning goal for Brazil.
</P>
<P>
His 25-meter shot went off the right post and the saving effort
from Schmeichel proved futile.
</P>
<P>
Marc Rieper almost equalized for Denmark in the 43rd minute but the
header hit the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's Cafu had a chance in the injury time but the ball was
saved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
